# A concise description of what this element means (e.g. for use in autogenerated summaries).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Encounter.extension:nprEpisodeIdentifier/short
msgid "Unik identifikator for episoden, som brukt i rapportering til Norsk pasientregister (NPR)."
msgstr "Unique identifier for the episode, as used in reporting to the Norwegian Patient Registry (NPR)."

# Provides a complete explanation of the meaning of the data element for human readability.  For the case of elements derived from existing elements (e.g. constraints), the definition SHALL be consistent with the base definition, but convey the meaning of the element in the particular context of use of the resource. (Note: The text you are reading is specified in ElementDefinition.definition).
#: StructureDefinition.element.Encounter.extension:nprEpisodeIdentifier/definition
msgid "Unik identifikator for episoden, som brukt i rapportering til Norsk pasientregister (NPR). Hvis det er registrert flere NPR-identifiere for samme episode lokalt, skal kun én NPR-identifikator angis ved innsending til Legemiddelregisteret (LMR). Velg enten den første eller den lokalt foretrukne identifikatoren. Den valgte identifikatoren skal oppgis med sin string-representasjon og/eller UUID-representasjon, dersom begge er tilgjengelige oppgis begge."
msgstr "Unique identifier for the episode, as used in reporting to the Norwegian Patient Registry (NPR). If multiple NPR identifiers are registered locally for the same episode, only one NPR identifier shall be submitted to the Medication Registry (LMR). Choose either the first or the locally preferred identifier. The selected identifier shall be provided using its string representation and/or UUID representation; if both are available, provide both."

